You are moving a column, aggregate or heading to a new location, independently
of any associated components.  Move the cursor to the new location and then use
the "Place" menu command to put the component there. 

To move a column or aggregate together with its associated headings, select 
the "Column" menu command, move the cursor to the new position, and then use 
"Place" or "Shift" to select the new location.  

The menu commands are:

        MENU COMMANDS   SYNOPSIS
        -------------   --------
        Place           Place the component alone at the current position.

        Left            Move the component alone to the left border of the 
                        report.

        Center          Center the component within the report.

        Right           Move the component alone to the right border of the 
                        report.

        Shift           Place the component alone at the current position,
                        shifting all components which are to the right.

        Column          Prepare to move the column or aggregate and all 
			headings associated with that component.  You will 
			be presented with a submenu for this selection.

        Help            Access the Ingres Help facility.

        End             Return to the Report Layout menu, without changing
                        the location of the component.
